{"first_name":"Raj","last_name":"Kapoor","permalink":"raj-kapoor","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/raj-kapoor","homepage_url":"","birthplace":"Bethlehem, PA","twitter_username":"Rajil","blog_url":"http://vcinme.typepad.com/vc/","blog_feed_url":"","affiliation_name":"Mayfield Fund","born_year":1970,"born_month":9,"born_day":26,"tag_list":"","alias_list":null,"created_at":"Thu Jul 12 05:18:14 UTC 2007","updated_at":"Wed May 30 08:46:04 UTC 2012","overview":"<p>VC and founder/CEO/entrepreneur Raj Kapoor joined Mayfield in 2005, bringing expertise in online advertising, e-commerce, consumer internet/digital media, social, mobile and internet infrastructure services and software.</p>\n\n<p>Raj sits on the boards of Zimride, Tagged, Fixya, Rubicon Project, Fanhood, and Wize.  He is also responsible for Mayfield&#8217;s investments in Chinese companies Qunar and Baihe.  In addition, he led the seed investments in Fivestars and Subtext.</p>\n\n<p>Most recently, Raj was co-founder and CEO of Snapfish, a leading global online photo service. Raj orchestrated the successful sale of Snapfish to Hewlett-Packard in March 2005.</p>\n\n<p>Prior to Snapfish, Raj was an executive at Excite@Home, where he led the company&#8217;s e-commerce and broadband applications business, driving new music, entertainment and e-commerce initiatives. Raj also held positions in strategic planning, business development and product management in consumer interactive television services at Bell Atlantic Corporation, which is now Verizon.</p>\n\n<p>Raj received an M.B.A. from Harvard Business School and a B.S. with honors in mechanical/robotics engineering from Carnegie Mellon University.</p>\n\n<p>He serves on the Carnegie Mellon Silicon Valley Advisory Council and the Harvard Business School&#8217;s California Research Center Advisory Board as well as on the board of Dosomething.org - the nation&#8217;s largest network of teens taking action for social causes.  Raj enjoys family, surfing, fitness, skiing, and singing in tech industry rock band - Coverflow (www.facebook.com/coverflow).</p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[111,150],"assets/images/resized/0001/0252/10252v1-max-150x150.jpg"],[[171,230],"assets/images/resized/0001/0252/10252v1-max-250x250.jpg"],[[171,230],"assets/images/resized/0001/0252/10252v1-max-450x450.jpg"]],"attribution":null},"degrees":[{"degree_type":"MBA","subject":"","institution":"Harvard Business School","graduated_year":1996,"graduated_month":null,"graduated_day":null},{"degree_type":"BS","subject":"Mech Eng/Robotics","institution":"Carnegie Mellon University","graduated_year":1992,"graduated_month":null,"graduated_day":null}],"relationships":[{"is_past":false,"title":"Managing Director","firm":{"name":"Mayfield Fund","permalink":"mayfield-fund","type_of_entity":"financial_org","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,56],"assets/images/resized/0000/0850/850v1-max-150x150.jpg"],[[217,82],"assets/images/resized/0000/0850/850v1-max-250x250.jpg"],[[217,82],"assets/images/resized/0000/0850/850v1-max-450x450.jpg"]],"attribution":null}}},{"is_past":false,"title":"board of directors","firm":{"name":"BigDeal","permalink":"bigdeal","type_of_entity":"company","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,42],"assets/images/resized/0006/6866/66866v1-max-150x150.jpg"],[[250,71],"assets/images/resized/0006/6866/66866v1-max-250x250.jpg"],[[277,79],"assets/images/resized/0006/6866/66866v1-max-450x450.jpg"]],"attribution":null}}},{"is_past":false,"title":"board of directors","firm":{"name":"FixYa","permalink":"fixya","type_of_entity":"company","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,54],"assets/images/resized/0000/0592/592v5-max-150x150.png"],[[250,90],"assets/images/resized/0000/0592/592v5-max-250x250.png"],[[267,97],"assets/images/resized/0000/0592/592v5-max-450x450.png"]],"attribution":null}}},{"is_past":false,"title":"board of directors","firm":{"name":"Zimride","permalink":"zimride","type_of_entity":"company","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,60],"assets/ima